{
  "texts": [
    "These digital learning platforms dominate the educational environment.",
    "Both blackboard-based instruction and mobile learning are digital learning platforms through which learners and teachers are allowed to attend/present their virtual classes, download/upload their assignments, participate in an online discussion, and get/offer in-time feedback (Mohsen & Shafeeq, 2014).",
    "According to Khafaga (2021), blackboard-based instruction offers students greater flexibility and equal participation in the learning process.",
    "Unlike face-to-face instruction, the use of blackboard collaborate and mobile phones in the learning and teaching process allows for the amalgamation and participation of a greater number of students that can be easily controlled, directed, and summoned for virtual discussions (Herwiana & Laili, 2022).",
    "According to Fredricks et al. (2004), students\" engagement refers to their attendance, grades, overall wellbeing, discussion involvement, learning self-efficacy, motivation, and academic performance."
  ]
}